transcript_text: If you want a big bench and arms that look thick while wearing even a loose t-shirt, you need to focus on building the  media head of a tricep. The part of your tricep that is closest to the elbow. Triceps are seriously underestimated by most people when it comes to bench strength.  Matt Wining and Louis Simmons both preach this and they know what they're talking about to say the least.  Due to the length tension relationship and where the different heads of the tricep attach, my favorite exercise to target the media head of the tricep is decline dumbbell skull crushers.  The dumbbell should start somewhere around your ear and end up in line with your forehead, but play around with it until you feel this attraction by your elbow.
